We start by computing each ratio using the end‐of‐period data:

1. Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
• Total Current Assets (end) = 9,963,057.95  
• Total Current Liabilities (end) = 829,755.77  
• Current Ratio = 9,963,057.95 / 829,755.77 ≈ 12.01

2. Inventory Turnover Ratio = Cost of Goods Sold / Average Inventory  
Since the beginning inventory is 0 and the ending inventory is 720,000, the average inventory is:  
• Average Inventory = (0 + 720,000) / 2 = 360,000  
• Cost of Goods Sold = 3,085,000  
• Inventory Turnover Ratio = 3,085,000 / 360,000 ≈ 8.57

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "12.01",
    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "8.57"
  }
}
